{
  "stem": "27507.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we were so unbelievably lucky from that point of view, because those were my uncles, they put the family in the shop.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Otherwise, it was terribly difficult.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "You had to pay money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And even then, it was lots of money.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And probably even then, it was not at all certain, because after all that you could get into a shop, and get an official identity, official card, official exemption, because after all those shops had a limited number of places.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And now, suddenly, probably 10 times as many people as there was place for wanted all to get permission to get in.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But already on the 21st of July, I think, we went to the shop, because we didn't stay in our house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I remember that there was the atmosphere, even on this first day when nobody yet was properly deported, or very few people were deported.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But the whole place was like in a state of complete panic.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Everywhere, people were everywhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And people were everywhere [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] frightened, terribly worried, terribly upset.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we walked through those streets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And in front of the Schultz shop in [POLISH] Street, there was, again, masses of people who were trying to break the door into the shop.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And there was some strong men standing kind of-- there was a shop who was called [?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Singer, ?] who was a German Jew, according to what I knew.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And they were pushing people inside, and beating people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It was really, absolutely horrendous, everything that was happening there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And those crowds and crowds of people who were trying to get into the shop, just like that, and being beaten, and being pushed, and being treated absolutely horribly.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
